The paper deals with object detection and localization using textual descriptions, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel approach to training a text-only classifier, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the use of freely available caption data, which relates to information retrieval (cs.IR).
